OL,6,FBrian Hegary, defending Ndela, said he
OL,7,Fhad acted with "breathtaking
OL,8,Fstupidity" and added: "It was not
OL,9,Fsomething that was particularly
OL,10,Fpreconceived. He was there for a
OL,11,Flawful purpose, a friend was taking a
OL,12,Fflight and it was spur of the moment
OL,13,Fto behave as they did."
OL,15,F"He intended to cause humour for
OL,16,Fpeople online. I know how stupid,
OL,17,Firresponsible and misjudged that was
OL,18,Fbut that was his primary motivation.
